# mails.com — full stack

Meta-repo orchestrates two **separate git repos**. Never commit `mails-backend/` or `mails-frontend/` from the workspace root.

| Folder | GitHub repo | Local port | Production |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `mails-backend/` | `mails-com/back` | `:3000` | Fly.io `mails-back.fly.dev` |
| `mails-frontend/` | `mails-com/front` | `:3001` | Cloudflare Workers `front.aitor.workers.dev` |

Deep dives: [`mails-backend/.cursor/rules/project-stack.mdc`](mails-backend/.cursor/rules/project-stack.mdc) (backend detail), [`mails-frontend/CONTRIBUTING.md`](mails-frontend/CONTRIBUTING.md) (frontend detail).

---

## Backend — Go + Fiber v3

**Module:** `github.com/mails-com/back` · **Go 1.26** · **Fiber v3** (handlers use `fiber.Ctx`, not `*fiber.Ctx`)

### Data layer

| Piece | Role |
| --- | --- |
| Postgres | Fly Managed Postgres, driver `pgx/v5` + `pgxpool` (no ORM) |
| goose | SQL migrations in `internal/db/migrations/` (`NNNN_desc.sql`) |
| sqlc | `internal/db/queries/*.sql` → `internal/db/generated/` (gitignored) |

**sqlc order:** always `sqlc generate` before `go build` / CI / Docker.

**Tables (goose):** `users`, `oauth_accounts`, `user_sessions`, `user_events`, `user_credits`, `credit_transactions`, `api_keys`. `fiber_sessions` is auto-created by the session storage driver.

### Package layout

```
cmd/api/main.go          entrypoint, routes, graceful shutdown, ./api migrate
internal/handler/        HTTP handlers, middleware, NewErrorHandler
internal/service/        credits, stripe, apikeys
internal/auth/           Google OAuth2, CSRF state, userinfo
internal/session/        Postgres-backed Fiber session (cookie session_id)
internal/db/             pool, migrate, migrations, queries
internal/ua/             user-agent → browser/OS/device_type
contracts/user.json      canonical User JSON (synced to frontend)
```

### Middleware chain (global)

1. CORS (`FRONTEND_URL` + `http://localhost:*`, credentials)
2. recover → logger → session
3. Route groups: `RequireAuth` (+ `TouchSession` on `/api`), `RequireAuthOrAPIKey` (+ limiter on `/v1`), `RequireAdmin` on `/admin`

### API surface (summary)

| Prefix | Auth | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `/ping`, `/health` | none | liveness / DB ping |
| `/auth/*` | session flow | Google OAuth, logout → 303 to API `/` |
| `/api/*` | session cookie | dashboard: me, sessions, credits, keys, billing portal |
| `/v1/*` | cookie or API key | `POST /v1/validate` — 60 req/min sliding window per user |
| `/admin/*` | session + admin role | gift credits (requires `ref_id`) |

**Errors:** `{"error":"<snake_code>","message":"<human>"}` via `handler.NewErrorHandler()`.

**User resource:** flat JSON `{id,email,name,avatar_url,role,locale,theme}` — contract in `contracts/user.json`.

**Credits:** atomic ledger (`user_credits` + `credit_transactions`); idempotency via `X-Idempotency-Key` → `ref_id` (409 on duplicate).

**API keys:** `mails_live_*` / `mails_test_*` + 64 hex; SHA-256 stored; Bearer or `X-API-Key` on `/v1`.

### Auth

- Login: browser redirect to `GET /auth/google` (not fetch)
- API calls from SPA: `fetch(..., { credentials: "include" })`
- Prod cookies: `SameSite=None; Secure` (cross-origin SPA ↔ API)
- Session: `IdleTimeout 7d`, `AbsoluteTimeout 30d`

### Env (server boot)

Required: `DATABASE_URL`, `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID`, `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET`, `BASE_URL`, `FRONTEND_URL`, `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`. Optional: `ENV`, `PORT`.

Migrate subcommand: only `DATABASE_URL`.

### Tooling & CI

| Tool | Role |
| --- | --- |
| air | local dev hot reload |
| Lefthook | pre-commit: gofumpt, goimports, golangci-lint v2 |
| GitHub Actions | sqlc → tidy → build → vet → test → lint; deploy Fly on push to `main` |

### Verify

```bash
cd mails-backend
sqlc generate   # after SQL query edits
go test ./...
go vet ./...
golangci-lint run
go build -o /tmp/mails-api-test ./cmd/api
```

